{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Task\n> Add auth to this API. The frontend uses cookies.\n\n## Orientation Findings\n1. The repository is empty -- only a \"seed\" commit exists with no source files. No API code, no package.json, no framework files, no routes.\n2. The only files present are `D-output.txt` (output from a prior unrelated session) and `E-output.jsonl` (session log). Neither contains API source code.\n3. The task says \"this API\" but no API implementation is discoverable. The plan must therefore be written as a generic blueprint applicable to a cookie-authenticated REST API, with per-step notes indicating where the implementer must adapt to the actual codebase.\n4. The only concrete constraint the user supplied: the frontend uses cookies (implying cookie-based session authentication, not token-in-header).\n\n## Question\nGiven that no API code exists in the repo, what is the correct sequence of steps to add cookie-based session authentication to a generic REST API? Assume Node.js/Express as the most common context unless your inspection suggests otherwise. Flag any steps that require the implementer to verify framework-specific details before acting."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012VaeBNdSKhdyqr6AC9NYqB","session_id":"a493c0c8-c9b3-44b2-a365-6f302f4b7041","uuid":"a2ef44f7-f148-4c39-b098-4f96f7fafb88","timestamp":"2026-04-24T07:36:45.342Z"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"abdb73aa149edf0b1","tool_use_id":"toolu_012VaeBNdSKhdyqr6AC9NYqB","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Advisor consultation: add cookie-based auth to an API","usage":{"total_tokens":15699,"tool_uses":0,"duration_ms":8230},"uuid":"c5b83494-9d75-4635-95f1-6125eeaf76b0","session_id":"a493c0c8-c9b3-44b2-a365-6f302f4b7041"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012VaeBNdSKhdyqr6AC9NYqB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Assuming Node.js/Express (unverified), do install `express-session`, `connect-redis`, `bcrypt`, and `redis`. Verify Node.js/Express before acting.\n2. Assuming HTTPS in production (unverified), do configure session cookies with `httpOnly: true`, `secure: true`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, and a 24h `maxAge`. Verify HTTPS before acting.\n3. Mount `express-session` with Redis store, a strong `SESSION_SECRET` from env, and `resave: false, saveUninitialized: false`.\n4. Implement `POST /login` (bcrypt compare, regenerate session, set `req.session.userId`), `POST /logout` (`session.destroy` + `clearCookie`), and `GET /me`.\n5. Add `requireAuth` middleware checking `req.session.userId`; apply to protected routes.\n6. Assuming same-origin frontend (unverified), do skip CSRF tokens and rely on `SameSite=Lax`; otherwise add `csurf`. Verify same-origin before acting.\n\n**Critical:** Confirm the actual framework (Fastify/Koa/Nest/Hono change every package choice) before step 1."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abdb73aa149edf0b1 (use SendMessage with to: 'abdb73aa149edf0b1' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 16111\ntool_uses: 0\nduration_ms: 8238</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a493c0c8-c9b3-44b2-a365-6f302f4b7041","uuid":"97d55ae4-0447-4121-a6c9-a22411c2dc1b","timestamp":"2026-04-24T07:36:53.579Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"## Task\n> Add auth to this API. The frontend uses cookies.\n\n## Orientation Findings\n1. The repository is empty -- only a \"seed\" commit exists with no source files. No API code, no package.json, no framework files, no routes.\n2. The only files present are `D-output.txt` (output from a prior unrelated session) and `E-output.jsonl` (session log). Neither contains API source code.\n3. The task says \"this API\" but no API implementation is discoverable. The plan must therefore be written as a generic blueprint applicable to a cookie-authenticated REST API, with per-step notes indicating where the implementer must adapt to the actual codebase.\n4. The only concrete constraint the user supplied: the frontend uses cookies (implying cookie-based session authentication, not token-in-header).\n\n## Question\nGiven that no API code exists in the repo, what is the correct sequence of steps to add cookie-based session authentication to a generic REST API? Assume Node.js/Express as the most common context unless your inspection suggests otherwise. Flag any steps that require the implementer to verify framework-specific details before acting.","agentId":"abdb73aa149edf0b1","agentType":"lz-advisor:advisor","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Assuming Node.js/Express (unverified), do install `express-session`, `connect-redis`, `bcrypt`, and `redis`. Verify Node.js/Express before acting.\n2. Assuming HTTPS in production (unverified), do configure session cookies with `httpOnly: true`, `secure: true`, `sameSite: 'lax'`, and a 24h `maxAge`. Verify HTTPS before acting.\n3. Mount `express-session` with Redis store, a strong `SESSION_SECRET` from env, and `resave: false, saveUninitialized: false`.\n4. Implement `POST /login` (bcrypt compare, regenerate session, set `req.session.userId`), `POST /logout` (`session.destroy` + `clearCookie`), and `GET /me`.\n5. Add `requireAuth` middleware checking `req.session.userId`; apply to protected routes.\n6. Assuming same-origin frontend (unverified), do skip CSRF tokens and rely on `SameSite=Lax`; otherwise add `csurf`. Verify same-origin before acting.\n\n**Critical:** Confirm the actual framework (Fastify/Koa/Nest/Hono change every package choice) before step 1."}],"totalDurationMs":8238,"totalTokens":16111,"totalToolUseCount":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15692,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":413,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch